1
00:00:00,110 --> 00:00:06,560
In this video, we are going to learn the challenges and disadvantages of microservice architectures.

2
00:00:06,920 --> 00:00:12,350
Microservices has significant benefits, but also has significant challenges.

3
00:00:12,350 --> 00:00:18,410
Moving from monolithic to microservices means a lot of more management complexity.

4
00:00:18,950 --> 00:00:24,260
Here you can see the some of the challenges we need to consider before applying the microservice architecture.

5
00:00:24,290 --> 00:00:26,750
The first challenge is complexity.

6
00:00:26,780 --> 00:00:32,900
Microservices application has lots of services need to work together and should create a volume.

7
00:00:33,020 --> 00:00:39,860
Since there are lots of services, that means there is more moving parts than the monolithic application.

8
00:00:39,890 --> 00:00:44,450
Each service is simpler, but the entire system is more complex.

9
00:00:44,540 --> 00:00:48,560
Even deployments can be complicated for hundreds of services.

10
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:49,910
Deployed different times.

11
00:00:49,910 --> 00:00:51,440
Hard to manage versions.

12
00:00:51,620 --> 00:00:53,480
Think about the communication.

13
00:00:53,480 --> 00:01:00,560
It is really easy to communicate components in monolithic application because it is inter-process communication.

14
00:01:00,560 --> 00:01:03,710
It can be same machine and same process.

15
00:01:03,710 --> 00:01:11,510
But in microservices, microservice communication is hard topic and need to have a strategy to manage

16
00:01:11,510 --> 00:01:16,790
interservice communications between server, even different geo locations.

17
00:01:18,200 --> 00:01:22,520
And the second challenges is network problems and latency.

18
00:01:22,550 --> 00:01:28,790
Since microservices are small and communicate with inter service communication, we should manage network

19
00:01:28,790 --> 00:01:29,600
problems.

20
00:01:29,630 --> 00:01:36,140
If we call chain of services for particular request, this will increase latency problems and need the

21
00:01:36,140 --> 00:01:39,500
correct design to APIs for proper communication.

22
00:01:39,620 --> 00:01:46,130
In order to avoid chatty API calls, you need to consider asynchronous communication patterns like message

23
00:01:46,130 --> 00:01:49,400
broker systems using publish subscribe patterns.

24
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:53,300
Another challenges is development and testing.

25
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:58,370
Think about the end to end process, one of the long business requirement.

26
00:01:58,400 --> 00:02:04,490
If the requirement touch on several microservice that need to act as a one application, it is hard

27
00:02:04,490 --> 00:02:09,020
to develop and testing these end to end processes in microservice architectures.

28
00:02:09,020 --> 00:02:16,280
If you compare to monolithic ones, existing tools are not always designed to work with service dependencies.

29
00:02:16,280 --> 00:02:19,640
Refactoring across service boundaries can be difficult.

30
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:25,760
So that means integration testing as well as the end to end testing can become more difficult and more

31
00:02:25,760 --> 00:02:27,980
important than ever in microservices.

32
00:02:29,150 --> 00:02:31,580
Another challenges is data integrity.

33
00:02:32,120 --> 00:02:37,760
Microservices has its own data persistence, so data consistency can be a challenge.

34
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:44,060
Mostly we should follow eventual consistency where it is possible, but transactional operations are

35
00:02:44,060 --> 00:02:45,800
always will be challenging.

